    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>Get Your Yearbook Ready</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20101028.png' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, October 28, 2010</b> &mdash;
    It&#039;s finally time to create your <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/yearbook/"> yearbook</a>, full of all your amazing accomplishments and unique style. So how does this fun, easy, yearbook-making process work? Starting today you can make as many printable <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/yearbook/"> yearbooks</a> as you wish through December 31st, 2010. This will include changing your Buddy&#039;s outfits as many times as you please. (Imagine wearing an astronaut outfit and then later changing into a crazy chicken outfit?) You can also change the exterior of your home as many times as you&#039;d like--maybe at times to match your outfit!<br><br>The more you do, the more you can take with you. Below is what you&#039;ll get and what you need to do:<br><br>* An image of you in front of your home. So this means you need to start shopping for a new outfit or putting a combination together that you may have never tried before.  Start decorating the outside of your home any way you want...the wackier the better!<br><br>* Your bio of interests and personality. So if you really like magic tricks and you haven&#039;t listed it yet, go back and <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_change.phtml/">customize your buddy traits</a> to switch it up.<br>
<br>
* Now is the time to choose your <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/inventory.phtml/">favorite 15 items!</a> Start thinking of what they&#039;ll be, shop at yard sales, and shop &#039;til you drop. <br><br>And remember you can do these actions as many times as you like until December 31st, 2010, resulting in hundreds of fun yearbook-printouts you can cherish.<br><br>And in case you missed last week&#039;s article, now is the time to take advantage of shopping for wacky items, playing new games to win new trophies, tending to your farm for new items, and visiting the Greenhouse to find bugs and grow flowers.<br><br>Congrats again grad, on all of the wonderful things you&#039;ve done in Millsberry!<br><br>Parents, please <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/parents/">click here</a>, for more info about the Millsberry graduation.
    </div>

